  "original_title": "\u0da2\u0db1\u0dcf\u0db0\u0dd2\u0db4\u0dad\u0dd2 \u0dbd\u0dda\u0d9a\u0db8\u0dca \u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dca\u0dba\u0dcf\u0dbd\u0dba\u0da7 \u0dad\u0ddc\u0dbb\u0dad\u0dd4\u0dbb\u0dd4 \u0db1\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0db0\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dd9\u0d9a\u0dca \u0db1\u0dd1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The Presidential Secretariat does not have an information officer",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "It is revealed in the Freedom of Information Commission that since Mr. Ranil Wickramasinghe assumed the office of the President, no information officer has been appointed in the Presidential Secretariat.",
        "This was revealed when an appeal filed with the Commission regarding the right to information was heard on 24.08.2022 due to the Presidential Secretariat's refusal to provide information to the request made under the Freedom of Information Act for the expenses incurred on behalf of the Presidential Commission appointed on behalf of the Easter Commission. .",
        "There, the Information Commission informed that since an information officer has not been appointed in the Presidential Secretariat, the appeal hearing will be adjourned in order to give them another chance.",
        "However, the refusal of the Presidential Secretariat to provide information regarding the said matter, as well as the fact that none of the authorized officers of the Presidential Secretariat did not participate in the appeal hearing held earlier on June 01, 2022, and subsequently did not participate in the appeal hearing on August 24, 2022, stating that an information officer had not been appointed. A strong point is that in the government of a president who made a strong political intervention to bring the right to information in this country.",
        "However, Section 23 (1) (b) of the Right to Information Act No. 12 of 2016 indicates that until an information officer is appointed in a public authority, the head or executive officer of a public authority shall be considered as the information officer of that public authority for the purposes of this Act. . as Accordingly, it appears that the President's Secretariat has also acted contrary to the instructions of the Information Act in not participating in the appeal hearing on that day saying that there is no information officer.",
        "However, an attempt was made to contact a responsible officer of the Presidential Secretariat to inquire about this, but it failed."
      ],
